    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–1849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-18">January 18,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received January 18—3:47 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>81. Newspaper Tientsin <hi rend="italic">Jih Pao</hi> carried following item
                        today:<note n="3" xml:id="d1301fn3">For information on Communist occupation
                        of Tientsin, see telegram No. 61, January 14, 10:45 p. m., <ref
                            target="#pg_48">p. 48</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Commander Nieh Jung-chen of the Peiping-Tientsin Garrison Headquarters in a
                        joint statement on January 15 with political member Po Yi-po announced that
                        the Liberation Army will accord protection to law-abiding foreign residents
                        in Tientsin, on the condition that they observe the provisions laid down in
                        the proclamations of the People’s Government, the Military Commission, and
                        the Garrison Headquarters.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
